T1  - Evaluating In-Role and Out-of-Role Performers
AU  - Moore, Dorothy P.
Y1  - 1984/09/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256048
DO  - 10.5465/256048
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 603
EP  - 618
VL  - 27
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Performance evaluation when in-role and out-of-role behavior are manipulated in a male sex-typed occupation was investigated. Level of performance (high and low), mode of behavior (masculine and feminine), and performer sex were manipulated. Results indicate that performance evaluation is a winnowing process wherein raters assign ratings on the level of performance and value masculine over feminine modes of behavior, especially for female high performers.
AB  - Performance evaluation when in-role and out-of-role behavior are manipulated in a male sex-typed occupation was investigated. Level of performance (high and low), mode of behavior (masculine and feminine), and performer sex were manipulated. Results indicate that performance evaluation is a winnowing process wherein raters assign ratings on the level of performance and value masculine over feminine modes of behavior, especially for female high performers.
