AU  - Balkin, David B.
Y1  - 1984/09/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256047
DO  - 10.5465/256047
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 591
VL  - 27
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examines the relationship of faculty unionism on satisfaction with pay and other job dimensions. Union faculty were more satisfied with their pay than were nonunion faculty. Other significant determinants of faculty pay satisfaction were pay level, tenure, job experience, and sex. With the exception of pay, unionization was unrelated to other dimensions of job satisfaction.
AB  - This study examines the relationship of faculty unionism on satisfaction with pay and other job dimensions. Union faculty were more satisfied with their pay than were nonunion faculty. Other significant determinants of faculty pay satisfaction were pay level, tenure, job experience, and sex. With the exception of pay, unionization was unrelated to other dimensions of job satisfaction.
