TY  - JOUR
T1  - Correlates of Voting Behavior in a Union Decertification Election
AU  - Bigoness, William J.
AU  - Tosi, Henry L.
Y1  - 1984/09/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256052
DO  - 10.5465/256052
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 654
EP  - 659
VL  - 27
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a study pertaining to the relationship between selected demographic and attitudinal variables and employee voting behavior in a union decertification election. The study was conducted at a public university in the southeastern U.S. The study results revealed that a positive attitude toward unions is strongly correlated with pro-union voting behavior. These findings support previous studies concerning voting behavior. No significant relationship was evident between salary and reported voting behavior.
AB  - The article presents a study pertaining to the relationship between selected demographic and attitudinal variables and employee voting behavior in a union decertification election. The study was conducted at a public university in the southeastern U.S. The study results revealed that a positive attitude toward unions is strongly correlated with pro-union voting behavior. These findings support previous studies concerning voting behavior. No significant relationship was evident between salary and reported voting behavior.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256052
